This paper deals with a problem of gathering a swarm of robots, which is a common topic in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS) and robotics. The problem involves coordination and communication among the robots, which are typical issues in MAS. Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves the movement and positioning of robots on a grid, which is related to robotics and control. Hence, cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely sub-category. The problem requires algorithms and data structures to be developed for efficient coordination and communication among the robots, which is related to distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another likely sub-category. The problem involves the manipulation of data structures and algorithms for efficient coordination and communication among the robots, which is related to data structures and algorithms. Hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the problem involves the synchronization and control of the robots, which is related to control theory and systems. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely sub-category.
